  <description><![CDATA[<p>Bregenz lies between the shimmering waters of Lake Constance and the greenery of the Pfänder mountain and Bregenz forest. This vibrant town is best known for the spectacular opera performances which take place annually on the biggest lake stage in the world during the renowned ‘Bregenzer Festspiele’. There are various lakeside cafés and restaurants and it’s easy to nip across the border into Germany to the north-west, Switzerland to the west and even Liechenstein to the south.</p>]]></description>
